answers.q: what does e403 mean on att air
answers.a: On a food label, E403 means ammonium alginate—a seaweed-derived thickener and stabiliser used to add viscosity and keep mixtures uniform; it’s unrelated to AT&T Air.
In food labelling, E403 isn’t an error code—it’s the additive code for ammonium alginate, a plant-derived thickener/stabiliser approved for use under good manufacturing practice.
